==What is Openttd.cfg?==

Openttd.cfg is the configuration file which OpenTTD uses to store all its settings. This file uses the INI-file structure that is common in Windows .INI files.  You can edit the file using Notepad or any Text Editor.

==How does it work?==

Each time you quit OpenTTD, it writes any changes to the cfg file.
The file has all the variables organised into groups to make it easier to edit.

